{
  "stem": "27340.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But, you know, young people have a [? throng, ?] a drive.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They always know what is best, and I remained determined.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In any case, there was no way of getting out of it because I'd already undertaken to serve the cause, whatever that cause was, which was totally unknown to me at the time.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My mother had a little twinkle in her eye.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She was rather more adventurous than my father.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My father was very conservative with a small C and always thought you do the right thing at the right time.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "For instance, to illustrate this, he would never come to a table at, at, at lunchtime without wearing a tie, no matter how hot the weather may have been.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He may have perhaps taken his tie off during the morning.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But for lunch-- just en famille, just he and his wife and perhaps myself and my brother, but he would be wearing a tie.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he also insisted on the boys always putting on a jacket.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] This was always a battle between us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My mother was far more advanced, something of a Bohemian, but you know, much more realistic and pragmatic about these things.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And while, of course, she didn't particularly like to see her son away for some period or so, I dare say she had some sort of an idea of what it was all about.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And so there was a twinkle in her eye almost as if to say, go in peace and do what you think you ought to be doing.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Indeed, that gave me a lot of encouragement.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My father wouldn't speak to me [LAUGHS] for two or three weeks before I finally said, this is it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Goodbye, see you in about six months' time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I was sent to France.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
